              <title xml:lang="per">&#x632;&#x627;&#x62F; &#x627;&#x644;&#x645;&#x633;&#x627;&#x641;&#x631;&#x64A;&#x646;</title>
              <note>
                <p>A guide to preservation of health and self-treatment for travellers, by Mu&#x1E25;ammad Mahd&#x12B; ibn &#x2018;Al&#x12B; Naq&#x12B;. The work was completed at Isfahan in 1141/1728, during the Afghan invasion, for <name type="person" role="patron" xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">M&#x12B;rz&#x101; Mu&#x1E25;ammad Ism&#x101;&#x2018;&#x12B;l</name>. </p>
                <p>It comprises two parts (ma&#x1E6D;lab): on preventive health and hygiene, and on the treatment of certain ailments treatable without the aid of a physician. </p>
                <p>The present manuscript is slightly incomplete at the end. </p>
              </note>
